        "content": "<p>If you have control of the <code>def</code>, naming the type class parameter (e.g. <code>[IsHom : IsHomLift p f' Ï†']</code>) lets you do <code>induceMap (IsHom := ...)</code>.</p>\n<p>If you do not, then the only way I can think of is to define an abbrev <code>induceMap'</code> that names the parameter and delegates to <code>induceMap</code> -- then you can use the trick above.</p>",
